Product name: Men's vintage Orient watch Diver watch Automatic watch Japanese watch Large watch Gift for him
Description:
The Orient Watch Company is one of the largest producers of mechanical watches in Japan. It is a wholly-owned subsidiary of Seiko Epson but designs and manufactures separately from Seiko. 
Needing an inexpensive modern movement for mass production, Orient licensed the Seiko 7006 movement design along with the Seiko 6600 Magic Lever automatic winding mechanism. These were combined to become the Orient 46 movement, which is still the company's mainstream automatic watch movement today. Orient also manufactures a number of other movements, including the high-end Orient 88700. 
Orient is unusual in that they produce all of their own movements, including most components, in-house.
The Japanese Orient diver automatic watch works and keeps time well. The black  dial has white indexes and it is in good condition, however the glass and the bezel show some age marks. It also has a date and a day windows at 3 o'clock with quick date set up. Some sizes for you 44mm bezel that rotates 48mm with case and crown guard, lug to lug 51mm, thickness around 13 mm.
The Orient comes with new N.D.LIMITS diver strap.
This watch will make a fine addition to any watch collection.
As a vintage watch the water resistance cannot be guaranteed.
Please also mind that any mechanical watch should be serviced regularly.

Product name: Hand Crafted BABY PLAYING an Original LITHOGRAPH Print By Maud Tausey Fangel
Description:
Up for sale is an original lithograph by Maud Tausey Fangel of a playing baby with special additions.   
Wikipedia " For a good part of the first half of the twentieth century, Ms. Fangel was the children's artist in our country -- her illustrations of ruddy-cheeked, doe-eyed, curly-locked children were everywhere. They set the standard for their day .... Many of Ms. Fangel's pictures were done in pastels, which allowed her to capture the movements of her young subjects in swift, impressionistic strokes. Most of Ms. Fangel's models were children from poor families, from orphanages, and settlement houses. Unaware of this, one newspaper referred to these children as "glamor babies." But Ms. Fangel understood the youngsters who sat and wiggled and dozed in the high chair for her a little more deeply than the correspondent: "I have a strange, persistent feeling that babies have a consciousness that we do not possess," she wrote. "They seem not yet to have lost an intelligence brought with them from another world. They are still wrapped in the mystery of their source." 
       My mom took this wonderful print and added her artistic touch.   She made the satin pillow and added a lace edging.   She also crocheted the baby sweater and baby booties and made the diaper and dress.  She then decoupaged the print with her special additions.    She made this to hang in my baby room in 1947.   It looks like she reframed it at one point and eventually it landed in the cedar chest.   I have it hanging in the bedroom now and  It comes from a Tabaco Free Home.  I do my best to describe each item as accurately as possible.   I take lots of pictures from lots of angles.  Please see the pictures for details as they are part of the description. If you can't see everything you want, I will be happy to send you more pictures. If you want more details please ask questions.   It  will be packed very carefully.  I will ship same day if cleared payment received before Noon, will ship next day if payment received after Noon.  Thanks for looking!

Product name: Mad Max: Fury Road - Nux's Bird Bobblehead
Description:
"What a day! What a lovely day!!"
Up for sale is a replication of the cobbled bobble-head bolted to Nux's dashboard, from the latest Mad Max installment, Fury Road.

Product name: Burgle Bros. Board Game Insert
Description:
This insert for the Burgle Bros. board game is designed to organize all the game components and still fit inside the unique box the game comes in.  It includes a bottom divider to hold the cards, room tiles, and walls and a top divider to hold the characters, guards, dice, and organize the game tokens.
If you select "Yes" for the "Sleeving your cards?" option you will receive the insert without the divider between the rooms and cards installed to accommodate the extra room needed for sleeved cards.  The divider will come loose with the insert should you want to install it later.
It is recommended to remove the cardboard spacer in the lid of box for use with this insert as shown in the last image.
FAQs
Burgle Bros. has been through two print runs and if you acquired the game after January 1st, 2017 it is likely you have a second printing.  The second print run had changes made to the components which required a redesign of the insert, thus the different layout.  If you are unsure of which printing you have take a look at the rulebook.  The second print run rulebook has 22 pages with page numbers at the bottom of each page while the first print run rulebook has 14 pages and no page numbers.
The first print version of the insert does not have a labeled space for the replacement tokens pack intended to replace the missing tokens from the second print run.  These tokens can be easily stored with the meeples however.  The replacement token pack can be found here should you need them (https://boardgamegeekstore.com/products/burgle-bros-replacement-chit-set-alter-ego).
Both versions of the insert are able to fit the promo event cards.  The promo pack can be found here (https://boardgamegeekstore.com/products/burgle-bros-5-promo-event-pack).

Product name: Glass Dip Pen - Calligraphy Pen
Description:
This listing is for one Romantic, marbled, hand-blown glass dip pen made in the Murano/Venetian style. These particular glass pens are very easy to write and draw with. They aren't too thick or heavy and each pen measures: 
7 1/2" x 5/8" x 5/8"
We currently have six different glass pen colors in stock:
• Red
• Multi Colored
• Green
• Black
• Red & Yellow
• Blue
Please choose your color before check-out. 
Glass ink pens were invented in during the height of the Renaissance in Venice, Italy. They were invented to solve the problem that many people had with quill pens and wooden dip pens in that the nibs would run out of ink too quickly, causing the writer to interrupt their work by frequently dipping the pen into the inkwell. 
These ingenious pen tips contain spiral grooves on the glass which holds more ink for a continuous flow. These pens were made to be dipped into ink bottles or inkwells. Ink also washes easily off of a glass pen and they are very easy to write and draw with because there is no nib or quill to split. (One just has to worry about them shattering if they are dropped.) 
The colors are marbled in the traditional Venetian glass blowing style. The entire pen is made of glass. 
Our pens come in a padded gift box with a piece of sandpaper for sharpening the tip of the pen. (Because these pens are made of glass, the tip can dull after use, one "sharpens" the pen by gently sanding the tip back into a point.) 
You will receive one pen and one gift box with your order, the inkwells and ink bottles are not included. You can however, purchase ink, paper and inkwells within our Arcane Objects Shop!
We can only accept returns or exchanges on art materials like this if they are returned in unused condition with packaging intact and in its original condition. (It needs to be like-new and in re-sellable condition).  If there is something wrong with the item or your order is incorrect, please contact us - we'd be happy to help! Please refer to our shop FAQs before ordering.
We do not offer international shipping for this item.

Product name: Slippery Elm Bark Organic Powder 1 oz
Description:
Slippery Elm Bark Organic Powder
Slippery Elm Bark is an herb derived from the inner part of the elm bark and is usually used as a finely ground powder. The chopped bark is suitable for poultices for cuts, wounds and burns. Slippery elm bark added to hot water has a slippery and mucilaginous consistency. It is considered to be a safe and gentle herb and is allergen free. The inner bark, normally ground into a powder has been used for a variety of medicinal purposes. 
Slippery Elm Bark is soothing to indigestion, gastritis and stomach upsets, to line the stomach and reduce inflammation. Slippery Elm Bark is also soothing for sore throats and helps to alleviate colic, coughs and bronchitis. The powdered form is commonly made into a tea with sweetener and milk. 
Slippery Elm Bark Powder can be added to natural toothpaste to relieve aching gums. It can also be added to bath tea recipes, salves, facial masks, soaps, bath bombs, and scrubs.
Botanical name: Ulmus rubra 
Common names: Slippery Elm herb, Red Elm, Moose Elm, Gray Elm, Soft Elm, Indian Elm 
Origin: United States
1 ounce bag.
